column20: Wagner cited "Oenothera sect. Pachylophus (Spach) Endlicher, Gen. pl. 1190. 1840", gave a full reference to the basionym, and thus inadvertently validated the name at the sectional rank.
Etymology: This orchid genus is found in West Kalimantan.

Etymology: "Seasonally dry tropical woodlands (caatinga) from the southwestern portion of the Southern Sertaneja Depression ... in south central Bahia and adjacent north central Minas Gerais, Brazil (Fig. 2), on calcium rich soils."
non Poa peruviana Jacq.  Eponymy: The specific epithet honors Dr. Oscar Tovar Serpa.  doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1600/036364412X616701
non Poa expansa J. F. Gmel. (1791).  Eponymy: The specific epithet honors Dr. Jason R Swallen who described the species for the first time.  doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1600/036364412X616701
non Poa densa Troitsky (1928). Etymology: The specific epithet congesta refers to the crowded, spike-like panicle. doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1600/036364412X616701
non Poa brevis Hitchc. (1927). Etymology: The specific epithet arcuata refers to the arcuate tips of the glumes.  doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1600/036364412X616701
non Poa longifolia Trin. (1836), nec Poa longifolia Hochst. ex A.Rich. (1851).  doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1600/036364412X616701
non Poa californica Steud. (1854). Eponymy: The specific epithet honors Thomas Nuttall who first described the species.  doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1600/036364412X616701

non Poa boliviensis Hack. (1912), nec Poa longiligula Scribn. & T.A. Williams (1899) Etymology: The specific epithet boliviana refers to the endemic distribution of the species.  doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1600/036364412X616701
non Poa pygmaea Buchanan (1880).  Etymology: The specific epithet deminuta refers to the small size of plants of the species. doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1600/036364412X616701

column20: Etymology: Named after the unequally and minutely undulate leaves, only present in the inner margins of the convolute leaf (aniso = differently; crispa: undulate; it refers to margin of the canaliculated leaves, only the inner one crispate).  doi:10.1600/
